# {{ .prefix }}-proposing-adr

<!-- awf:section positioning -->
Writes a new ADR to `{{ .layout.adrDir }}/NNNN-kebab-title.md` (status `Proposed`) and commits it. Scope each record to a single load-bearing commitment: one decision per ADR. See `{{ .layout.workflowRef }}` for the full lifecycle rules and `{{ .prefix }}-adr-lifecycle` for state transitions.
<!-- awf:end -->

## When to invoke

<!-- awf:section when-to-invoke -->
Per `{{ .layout.workflowRef }}`: load-bearing decisions only, one ADR per decision. Bugfixes and routine refactors do not need an ADR. When in doubt, write the ADR.

